column1: #Name and contact info: Sara Helms Cahan; scahan@uvm.edu
#Study name:Hsp modulation of two ant species (Aphaenogaster picea and A. rudis)
#Financial support: National Science Foundation, Division of Environmental Biology#(1136644)
#Methods of data collection: Ants were collected along the eastern US and reared under common garden conditions in 2013

#Experimental units for each variable:Colony= colony identification, qpcr_block: is the randomized block design for qPCR; FC_83= fold induction for Hsp83; FC_70=fold change for Hsp70; FC_40= fold change for Hsp40; B_83= basal expression(delta delta CT method with the mean as the reference) Hsp83; B_70= basal expression(delta delta CT method with the mean as the reference) Hsp70; B_40= basal expression(delta delta CT method with the mean as the reference) Hsp40
